New Records: Morocco equalled the biggest winning margin in 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers with a 5-0 victory over Central African Republic.
Serhou Guirassy scored the first hat-trick in 2025 qualifying for Guinea against Ethiopia.
Key Match Events: Morocco led 4-0 by half-time in their match against Central African Republic.
Serhou Guirassy converted an 18th-minute penalty and scored two more goals to complete his hat-trick.
Pre-Game Insights: Morocco were heavily favored with a 114-place gap in Group B standings, making the outcome predictable.
Post-Match Reflections: Morocco's victory secured automatic qualification for the AFCON as hosts, with the tournament set to span two years for the first time.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match marked Morocco's highest winning margin in 2025 qualifiers, following South Africa's previous five-goal drubbing of Congo.
